%S A098348 1,2,3,4,8,13,8,20,44,75,16,48,132,308,541,32,112,368,1076,2612,4683,
%T A098348 64,256,976,3408,10404,25988,47293,128,576,2496,10096,36848,116180,
%U A098348 296564,545835,256,1280,6208,28480,120400,454608,1469892,3816548,7087261
%N A098348 Triangular array read by rows: T(n, k) = number of ordered factorizations of a "hook-type" number with n total prime factors and k distinct prime factors. "Hook-type" means that only one prime can have multiplicity > 1.
%C A098348 The first three columns are A000079, A001792 and A098385.
%C A098348 The first four diagonals are A000670, A005649, A172110 and A172111.
%C A098348 A070175 gives the smallest representative of each hook-type prime signature, so this sequence is a rearrangement of A074206(A070175).
%F A098348 T(n,k) = 1 + (Sum_{i=1..k-1} binomial(k-1,i)*T(i,i)) + (Sum_{j=1..k} Sum_{i=j..j+n-k-1} binomial(k-1,j-1)*T(i,j)) + (Sum_{j=1..k-1} binomial(k-1,j-1)*T(j+n-k,j)). - _David Wasserman_, Feb 21 2008
%F A098348 T(n,k) = A074206(2^(n+1-k)*A070826(k)). - _David Wasserman_, Feb 21 2008
%F A098348 The following conjectural formula for the triangle entries agrees with the values listed above: T(n,k) = Sum_{j=0..n-k} 2^(n-k-j)*binomial(n-k,j)*a(k,j), where a(k,j) = 2^j*Sum_{i=j+1..k+1} binomial(i,j+1)*(i-1)!*Stirling2(k+1,i). See A098384 for related conjectures. - _Peter Bala_, Apr 20 2012
%F A098348 T(n,k) = Sum_{i=1..n} Sum_{j=1..i} (-1)^(i-j)*j^(k-1)*binomial(i,j)*binomial(n+j-k,j-1). - _Ridouane Oudra_, Mar 18 2026
%e A098348 T(4,2) = 20 because 24=2*2*2*3 has 20 ordered factorizations and so does any other number with the same prime signature.
